arch:property.oc:show_val: This unit is part of the midden that includes 4121. It is the layer from the top of a wall on the south side of the space. Taxa represented are cattle, equids and sheep/goat as well as one bird bone and a possible fox. The larger animals are represented almost entirely by skull and feet bones, although there are rib and long bone fragments. The sheep and goat are more widely represented and there are numerous cut marks especially on the ribs implying post-consumption deposition for some of the bones. There are two fragments of worked bone both of which appear to have been broken predepositionally perhaps during production, as well as part of a bone ring. In summary the midden appears to contain butchery discards, post-consumption discards and discards from worked bone production. The relatively uniform condition of the bone and the lack of scavenging suggests fairly rapid burial after deposition. Last Number = 151

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
